<h2 id="lazio">Lazio</h2>

<p><b> Tarquinia </b></p>
<ul>
  <li>Etruscan Tombs: In Tarquinia, we explored ancient Etruscan tombs, and while the tombs held their secrets, they couldn‚Äôt hide the delightful aroma of lamb dishes wafting through the town.</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Rome</b></p>
<ul>
  <li>Saltimbocca Near Trajan Column: Our culinary adventure in Rome led us to enjoy saltimbocca near the Trajan Column, a dish that seemed to jump straight into our hearts with its flavors.</li>
  <li>Calzone with Ricotta: At Piata Navarro, we indulged in calzone with rich ricotta cheese, like a savory envelope filled with Roman love.</li>
  <li>Roma Tripes: We ventured into trying Roma tripes, a dish that made us feel like true Romans, embracing their culinary heritage.</li>
  <li>Gelato Pistacchio: Our sweet journey continued with gelato pistacchio, bought from Treviso and finished on the Spanish Steps. It was like a cool breeze on a warm Roman night.</li>
</ul>

